6:
Ready to get your ass handed to
you?
10:
Hah. Did I hit your head too hard last
time? Make you forget how you
keep losin' to me over and over?
14:
Those two really do get along
swimmingly, don't they? It seems
like they're going at it every day.
17:
Yep... I've lost count how many times
they've fought since they first met.
23: What's this? The crowd's all riled up.
27:
Some sort of fighting competition,
maybe? Let's stick around and see!
30:
Oh man, Ricardo is such a champ!
Really takes after his old man.
31:
Taking after him isn't enough! I need
him to be BETTER than his dad. I've
got tons of money riding on this kid!
33:
I'm gonna enjoy beating in that
smug face of yours, Ricardo.
36:
You again? Give me a break. At least
try to last ten seconds this time, all
right?
39: Shut your mouth, you stupid brat—
44:
Nope, not even close to ten. That's
just embarrassing.
50: Oy. You a slave too, kid?
53: What? Who the hell are you?
56:
So you're not, huh? You sure do fight
like one.
60:
Beastfolk, eh? Not sure what you
think you're doing here, but this isn't
a petting zoo.
76:
All right, everyone, get your money
ready. We've got a new match—the
mysterious Tiger-Man vs. Ricardo!
Place your bets now!
78:
Ooh, I'm betting all I've got on
Ricardo!
79:
Same! Put me down for Ricardo. He's
got this in the bag!
83:
Tch... I guess I have no choice but to
fight. I won't be going easy on you,
pussycat.
86: Didn't ask you to, daddy's boy.
91:
Huh. You've got good reflexes. Must
be all that mouse-catching you do.
94:
You're fast. Must be all that running
from your problems you do.
97:
Damn, that tiger has moves! He's
keeping up with Ricardo...
109:
That grim-ass look on your face!
Your heart's not in this. What the hell
are you even fightin' for?
121:
That's enough for me. This ain't a
real fight.
129:
Keep on fighting for your daddy,
kid.
I'm out.
136:
What's going on?! Do you have any
idea how much money I've got
riding on this?!
137:
Get that stupid tiger! Finish the
damn fight!
140:
Why are you just standing there?
You think I'm going to let you lose to
that tiger in front of everyone? Go
after him!
141:
Have you forgotten everything I
taught you?!
